# Data Model — NYC 311 Pipeline

```
Raw BigQuery Table (loaded by dlt)
  └── nyc_311_analytics.service_requests
            │
            ▼
  Staging Layer (views)
  └── stg_311_requests          ← casts types, filters nulls, standardises names
            │
            ▼
  Intermediate Layer (views)
  └── int_311_cleaned           ← DATE casts, resolution_time_hours, drops null boroughs
            │
       ┌────┴─────────────────────────────────┐
       ▼                                      ▼
  Marts Layer (tables)               Marts Layer (tables)
  ├── fact_311_complaints            ├── complaints_by_type
  │     partitioned by date          ├── complaints_by_borough
  │     clustered by borough,        └── complaints_over_time
  │     complaint_type
  └── dim_borough
```

## Layer descriptions

| Layer | Materialisation | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| staging | view | 1-to-1 with source; type casts and null filters only |
| intermediate | view | Business logic, calculated fields, joins |
| marts | table | Aggregated, dashboard-ready; partitioned & clustered for cost efficiency |

## Key design decisions

- **Partition key:** `DATE(created_date)` — BigQuery only scans the date partitions touched by a query, dramatically reducing cost for time-range filters.
- **Cluster keys:** `borough, complaint_type` — speeds up `GROUP BY borough` and `GROUP BY complaint_type` aggregations used by every dashboard chart.
- **Write disposition:** dlt loads with `append` — historical records accumulate without re-fetching old data.
- **Source of truth:** `stg_311_requests` is the single entry point for all downstream models; nothing reads directly from the raw table.
